Most attached project Im working on with HSF is “Free Master Class”
.

Btw the age of 9-19, who majored in Ballet can come join my class for Free.
We started small but now (after 9 yrs!!) It is 2 weeks long program and managed to meet hundreds of young and talented dancers every year.
.
The class isn’t only about ballet technique but the HOPE and COURAGE that one day with good training + work ethic Their Dreams also can be True like mine!
.
During 2022 Free Master class HSF visited,
4 art schools where we sponsor annual scholarships. 
3 different cities. About 400 students.
.
What we do isn’t possible with generous help from schools and teachers donation of their studio space. Thank you 😊 and Can’t wait till meet you all again for 2023 Masterclass 🩰💃🕺🪩

❤️. Hee and team @heeseofoundation

.
We also Thank @hyundai @genesis_seoul for sponsoring our masterclass tour! @heeseofoundation

When Tchaikovsky died in 1893, Marius Petipa began to search for composers for his ballets.  One of those to whom he turned was Alexander Glazunov, who was not yet thirty, but who had been one of the most gifted protégés who already enjoyed a considerable international reputation.

2023 YGP Korea will take place in Seoul, Korea from August 3rd-5th. 
Two days of master class followed by competition where we will choose annual scholarship recipients. Scholarship varies from tuition to their own school to study abroad at some of the most prestigious ballet schools in the world. I’m excited for all the amazing opportunities as well as meeting them in person! 
You can find detailed information at @heeseofoundation link bio.

Freddy married me on my NY premiere of Juliet. Thank you @rosalieoconnorphotography for your post so I can miss him dearly today! Sharing beautifully written Bill’s tribute here. 
.

Frederic Franklin

1914-2013
After 80 years on stage his presence was such that all he had to do was raise his arm and they would applaud. Of course he did more. He personified dance and much of 20th century dance history. Agnes de Mille called him the “inner motor of the Ballet Russe”. A pioneer of dance in America he danced, directed, staged, choreographed, performed and taught with amazing enthusiasm and generosity. He loved his art and lived for it. That love was returned and his memory lives. Here he is in ABT’s Romeo and Juliet, about to raise his arm.

Bill Ausman
